Myth: The flying fish danced between the sea and the sky, their delicate wings carrying them above the dark ocean waves to bathe in Elara’s silver moonlight. Yet, as they ventured closer to the rugged coastlines, Kaelen noticed that the wild coastal winds often blew these tiny acrobats off course, dangerously close to the jagged, unforgiving rocks hidden in the darkness.

To protect their winged ambassadors, Kaelen and Elara sought to illuminate the treacherous shores. Elara wept tears of pure, condensed moonlight, letting them fall like a gentle rain upon the shallow coves. As the silver droplets hit the water, Kaelen caught them in the gentle coastal eddies, preventing them from sinking into the sand. 

He breathed life into these lunar tears, transforming them into microscopic, floating lanterns that coated the surface of the coastal waters. Whenever the flying fish or the ocean's currents disturbed them, these tiny lanterns would erupt into a brilliant, neon-blue glow. 

Today, we call this enchanting phenomenon bioluminescence. It transforms the dark shores into glowing, starry pathways, safely guiding the ocean's wanderers away from danger. It remains a radiant reminder of the moon and sea working together to protect the life they cherish.

